<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Characteristic Species</h4>
	<div class="text"> <i>Potamogeton</i> spp., <i>Stuckenia</i> <i>pectinata</i> or other <i>Stuckenia</i> species is dominant or co-dominant at or below the water surface or as emergents with <i>Agrostis</i> <i>stolonifera</i>, <i>Bolboschoenus</i> <i>maritimus</i>, <i>Ceratophyllum</i> <i>demersum</i>, <i>Cotula</i> <i>coronopifolia</i>, <i>Eleocharis</i> <i>macrostachya</i>, <i>Elodea</i> spp. and <i>Lemna</i> spp. </div>
</div>

        
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Vegetation Layers</h4>
	<div class="text">  Herbs < 1 m; cover is open to continuous. </div>
</div>

        
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Membership Rules</h4>
	<ul class="text">
		
		<li><i>Potamogeton</i> spp. > 50% relative cover below and on the water surface (Holstein 2000).</li>
		
		<li><i>Stuckenia pectinata</i> > 30% relative cover with emergent plants present (Pickart 2006).</li>
		
		<li><i>Stuckenia pectinata</i> > 50% relative cover below the water surface (Hickson and Keeler-Wolf 2007).</li>
		
	</ul>
</div>

        
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Habitats</h4>
	<div class="text"> Slightly brackish pools, channels, or sloughs at intermediate tidal elevations; freshwater lakes. The USFWS Wetland Inventory (1996 national list) recognizes <i>Stuckenia pectinata</i> as an OBL plant. </div>
</div>

        
